               <p>I live in <placeName id="t17770409-5-crimeloc26">Drury-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17770409-5-crimeloc26" type="placeName" value="Drury-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17770409-5-crimeloc26" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17770409-5-off23 t17770409-5-crimeloc26"></join>: I am a <rs id="t17770409-5-deflabel27" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17770409-5-defend41 t17770409-5-deflabel27"></join> to Mrs. Walley; my mistress took the prisoner in out of charity; she was there about ten days; on the 26th of March I got up about eight o'clock and found the back part of the house left open and the prisoner gone: the things mentioned in the indictment were missing; I had seen them in my box on the evening; she was taken the same day at a puppet-show in St. James's-street, by 
               <persName id="t17770409-5-person45">
                  John
                   Scott
               <interp inst="t17770409-5-person45" type="surname" value="Scott"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17770409-5-person45" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17770409-5-person45" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , with a gown, a petticoat, a cap and apron of mine on; she said, she was surprized any body should accuse her, that they were her own cloaths: she had talked of going to the puppet-show the night before, which gave me a suspicion we should find her there.</p>
               <p>
            
